title: Lefties Losing It: ‘New low’ as Democrat asks ICE chief if he’s going to hell
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has blasted a Democrat for reaching a “new low” after she asked boss of ICE if he was going to hell.

title: Lefties Losing It: Even CNN is calling out the Democrat’s ICE lies
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has reacted to CNN call out Minneapolis Mayor Jacob Frey’s lies about ICE.

title: ‘Infiltrated by organised crime’: Corruption inquiry into CFMEU analysed
description: Shadow Industrial Relations and Employment Minister Tim Wilson sits down with Sky News host Peta Credlin to go over a landmark corruption inquiry into the CFMEU. ​

title: ‘Grubby and selfish’: TV host attacks Andrew and Fergie for relationship with Epstein
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi calls Sarah Ferguson and her ex-husband, former prince Andrew, “grubby and selfish”.  “The pair knew of Epstein's vile activities and continued to grow their relationship with him,” Ms Panahi said.   “So much of the communication we’ve read is after he was convicted on some really serious and ugly charges.”

title: Bombshell Epstein files reveal Sarah Ferguson proposed to sex offender
description: Psychiatrist and author Carole Lieberman discusses the latest batch of documents from the Epstein files, which reveal Sarah Ferguson proposed to convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein on at least two occasions.   “It was after he was convicted the first time … so obviously that didn't bother her very much,” Ms  Lieberman said.   “She does have this pattern where she’s attracted to men  … for what they can offer her.  “Apparently, Epstein actually did give her money on many occasions.”

title: ‘Not a great look’: Shocking footage shows King Charles heckled over Andrew-Epstein scandal
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi takes a look at footage of King Charles being heckled over former prince Andrew’s relationship with Jeffrey Epstein, despite his “nuclear call” to publicly condemn his brother.   “Despite that rather strong response, the King has been heckled during a visit to Lancashire by a man demanding to know how long he had known about Andrew and Jeffrey Epstein,” Ms Panahi said.   “Not a great look for the Royal Family.”

title: One Nation surges in polls just ‘two points’ behind Labor
description: Sky News host Andrew Bolt says Pauline Hanson's One Nation Party has surged in the latest polling, just “two points” behind Labor.  “One nation, despised by much of the media, led by a woman they'd mocked for decades, is now almost as popular in the polls as the giant Labor Party of Anthony Albanese,” Mr Bolt said.  “How rotten does this government seem to most voters. How p’d off voters must be with it that Labor's support in this poll is barely ahead of One Nation?”

title: Sky News Pulse: One Nation continues to ‘hit new highs’
description: Sky News host Paul Murray analyses Sky News Pulse indicating One Nation is continuing to soar while others plummet.

title: Trump: 80 per cent of Gaza casualties were ‘terrorists’
description: Sky News host Freya Leach analyses United States President Donald Trump claiming 80 per cent of Gaza casualties were terrorists.

title: ‘The numbers, as always, matter’: Angus Taylor aims for Liberal leadership position
description: On tonight’s episode of Paul Murray Live, Sky News host Paul Murray discusses Angus Taylor’s bid to take leadership of the Liberal Party, cost of living, US politics and more.

title: Grace Tame’s antisemitic chant is ‘unbecoming of an Australian of the Year’
description: NSW Opposition Leader Kellie Sloane says Grace Tame’s antisemitic chant in which she called to globalise the intifada, is “unbecoming of an Australian of the Year”.

title: ‘I think he will defeat Sussan’: Angus Taylor quits Liberal Party frontbench
description: Sky News host Freya Leach questions Opposition Leader Sussan Ley’s leadership in support for Angus Taylor.  This comes amid Angus Taylor’s decision to quit the Liberal Party frontbench.  “I think he will defeat Sussan. What is Sussan’s value proposition at this point? The status quo?” Ms Leach said.  “It will come down to a couple of swing MPs that aren’t locked in behind either leader … it’s hard to see how things could get much worse for the Liberal Party?”

title: Zuckerberg leaves California to avoid wealth tax, buys Florida ‘billionaire bunker’
description: Sky News host Freya Leach details how Mark Zuckerberg has left California and bought a multi-hundred-million-dollar house in Florida named the “billionaire bunker” to avoid a one-off five per cent wealth tax in California.   “Mark Zuckerberg is upping and leaving California, he’s just bought a multi-hundred-million-dollar house in Florida, which is now been nicknamed the ‘billionaire bunker’,” Ms Leach said.  “It’s because there’s pressure mounting in California to implement a one-off five per cent wealth tax on everyone with a net worth of over $1 billion.”

title: ‘Huge news’: FBI releases chilling footage of key suspect in Guthrie kidnapping
description: Sky News contributor Kosha Gada details how the FBI have released chilling footage of the key suspect in the kidnapping of Nancy Guthrie.    “This was huge news just breaking a few hours ago,” Ms Gada told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “They were able to recover four still images and two video clips from the Nest cameras.”

title: ‘All sorts of rumours flying’: Man detained in Nancy Guthrie case
description: Sky News contributor Kosha Gada says a man has been detained in the Nancy Guthrie case.   “The fact that he wasn’t held means they didn’t have probable cause … they also executed a search warrant on a property … where allegedly this person’s mother-in-law lived,” Ms Gada told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “They don’t have enough evidence to further arrest him, but they did detain him and question him, and we don’t know much else at this point.”
